data.text:
What Does the Name Brooke Mean?

Brooke is a gender-neutral name of German and Old English origin, meaning "small stream." It is particularly common as a girls' name, and was popularized in the U.S. by actress Brooke Shields.

How Popular is the Name Brooke?

Brooke is the #259 most popular girls' name in the U.S., according to 2021 Social Security Administration data. It was very popular in the year 2000, ranking #51, and has since slowly declined in popularity. However, it ranks #12 on FamilyEducation.com.

According to Google search data analysis, in the last five years Brooke was at its peak popularity in October 2019.

Popularity of the Name Brooke in the United States

The name Brooke was searched for most often in the following states:

West Virginia

Kentucky

Pennsylvania

Washington

Connecticut

Famous People Named Brooke and Brooke in Pop Culture

Famous Brooke's include actress Brooke Shields, actress Brooke Adams, model Brooke Burns, Olympic swimmer Brooke Bennett, and Dance Moms star Brooke Hyland.

The name Brooke features in TV, movies, and books, including One Tree Hill, Scream, and The Bold and the Beautiful.
